svg.title: Hours of daylight vs latitude vs day of year
svg.desc: A contour plot of the hours of daylight as a function of latitude and day of a typical non-leap year, using the most accurate models described in Sunrise equation, drawn by CMG Lee based on http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Hours_of_daylight_vs_latitude_vs_day_of_year.svg . Latitude 40Â° N (approximately New York City, Madrid and Beijing) is highlighted for reference.
